---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { updateReport } from '../lib/promotions';
import { lastUpdatedLabel } from '../lib/content';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Methodology | Healthcare Deals Canada"
  description="How Healthcare Deals Canada tracks current promotions for healthcare professionals in Canada."
>
  <section class="hero hero--detail">
    <div class="hero-main">
      <span class="hero-tag">Methodology</span>
      <h1>What gets published, what gets held back, and how the weekly refresh works.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
      The directory is intentionally curated. It only publishes promotions discovered on official Canadian source pages
      that pass pattern checks during the latest successful run.
      </p>
    </div>
    <aside class="hero-sidebar">
      <div class="hero-sidebar-header">
        <span class="hero-sidebar-label">Current Run</span>
        <span class="hero-sidebar-time">{lastUpdatedLabel(updateReport)}</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-sidebar-body">
        <div class="hero-sidebar-finding">{Math.round(updateReport.sourceSuccessRate * 100)}% source success on the latest refresh.</div>
        <div class="hero-sidebar-source">{updateReport.activeCount} active offers · {updateReport.sourceCount} tracked sources</div>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="page-grid">
      <article class="page-card prose-panel">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">Publication Policy</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Only official Canadian pages can create a public entry.</h2>
      <p>
        Public offers come only from a maintained registry of official provider pages. We do not auto-publish from open
        web search results, aggregator pages, or affiliate listings.
      </p>
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Update Cycle</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">The refresh is scheduled, validated, and then committed back into git.</h2>
      <p>
        A GitHub Action runs every Monday at 13:00 UTC. It refreshes all curated sources, validates the generated data,
        builds the Astro site, and commits the new outputs back to the repository only if the safety gates pass.
      </p>
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Safety Gates</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Bad refreshes are blocked before they can touch production.</h2>
      <p>
        Auto-publish stops if curated source success falls below 75% or if active offers fall more than 40% without a
        matching set of explicit expiries. That keeps bad parser runs from wiping the public directory.
      </p>
      </article>
      <aside class="page-card meta-panel">
        <dl>
          <div>
            <dt>Last update run</dt>
            <dd>{lastUpdatedLabel(updateReport)}</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Tracked sources</dt>
            <dd>{updateReport.sourceCount}</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Source success rate</dt>
            <dd>{Math.round(updateReport.sourceSuccessRate * 100)}%</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Gate status</dt>
            <dd>{updateReport.okToPublish ? 'Publishable' : 'Blocked'}</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
